page_content='Given  its  lengthy  history  of  occupation  and  high  archaeological  potential  (confirmed  by 
archaeological excavation), the site has the potential to yield information that will contribute to 
an understanding of Victoria’s cultural history. 

How is it significant? The Former McAteer Farming Complex site is of archaeological, historical, 
scientific, and social significance at a local level. 

Why is it significant? 

Aesthetic 

The bluestone cottage and outbuilding have been demolished, and the associated vegetation has 
been removed. Consequently, the site has been determined as having low aesthetic significance.

page_content='Archaeological investigations - conducted under C1699, C1710, and C1728 - have resulted in 
new information regarding the site, much of which has now been destroyed (see Section 3). 

Following  completion  of  the  post-excavation  programme  of  works,  the  cultural  heritage 
significance  of  the  site  has  been  reassessed  -  using  the  Heritage  Council  of  Victoria’s  (2008, 
2020)  ‘Heritage  Assessment  Criteria’  -  against  the  categories  set  out  in  Heritage  Victoria’s 
(2015a: 8) Guidelines for Investigating Historical Archaeological Artefacts and Sites below.
